It was indeed ready right on time. My only problem was there were multiple mistakes with my order. I understand it was a large order so could have been overwhelming but it was still disappointing. I ordered a basket of shrimp that was completely missing and had a member of my party that ordered it specifically because they don't eat chicken so was of course sad they forgot their food as they had nothing else they could eat. I'll definitely try again though as the food was good and service was good as well I'll just be sure to check the bag before leaving.

I grew up eating Church's Chicken, and I pick some up whenever I'm down south or in the Philly area. What I got today from the Church's restaurant on Minnesota Avenue was tied with the worse I've ever had. The other was L'enfant Plaza.  First of all,  the fries were awful. Crinkle fries are my favorite, so you can just imagine my disappointment  The fries were stale and soft, not crispy at all.  The batter on the chicken was too thick.  It was cooked hard on the outside, and not done all the way on the inside...a very amateurish error  I don't know what recipe they are following, but it's not close to Church's flavor or standard.  I am giving 1 star solely for the biscuits.  Neither of the 2 Church's restaurants in DC deserve the Church's name. Don't waste your time or money unless both restaurants are willing to get and follow proper training
